-- Marinade preparationCombine @ketchup{2%dl}, @water{2%dl}, @vinegar{2%tbsp}, @worcestershire sauce{2%tsp}, @finely chopped onion{2%tbsp}, @crushed garlic clove{1}, @brown sugar{2%tsp}, @honey{1%tbsp}, @dry yellow mustard{1%tsp}, @chili powder{3/4%tsp} or @allspice{1/4%tsp}, @cayenne pepper{1/4%tsp}, @oregano{1%tsp}, and @cumin{1%pinch} in a #saucepan.Simmer the @marinade{} for ~{15%minutes}.-- Ribs preparationPreheat #oven to ~{180-200%C}.Place @pork ribs{1.5%kg} on a #grill rack set over a #baking pan.Rub the @ribs{} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.Place the #baking pan with @ribs{} in the bottom of the #oven.When the @meat{} is warm, baste it with the prepared @marinade{}.Bake for ~{30-45%minutes} on each side.-- Grilling alternativeThe @ribs{} can also be cooked on a #grill.Pre-baking is still recommended.Grill the @ribs{} maintaining a good distance from the @coals{}.